info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued September 22 at 9:36PM EDT until September 24 at 5:00AM EDT by NWS Baltimore/Washington
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM EDT SUNDAY... * WHAT...Up to one half foot of inundation above ground level expected in low lying areas due to tidal flooding. * WHERE...In Maryland, Prince Georges County. In Virginia, Fairfax, Stafford and Central and Southeast Prince William/Manassas/Manassas Park Counties. * WHEN...Until 5 AM EDT Sunday, especially around the time of high tide. * IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only isolated road closures expected.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
